sentence: Joe Engle was the commander of two Space Shuttle missions including STS-2, the program's second orbital flight.
During the Shenzhou 7 mission in 2008, Zhai Zhigang became the first Chinese citizen to carry out a spacewalk.
2019 van Albada was discovered on 28 September 1935, by Dutch astronomer Hendrik van Gent at Leiden Southern Station, annex to the Johannesburg Observatory in South Africa.
NGC 172 is a spiral galaxy located around 136 million light-years away in the constellation Cetus.

Soyuz TMA-20 lifted off from the Baikonur Cosmodrome in Kazakhstan on December 15, 2010, and docked with the ISS two days later.
Fyodor Yurchikhin served as Soyuz Commander for his fourth mission aboard Soyuz TMA-09M, as Flight Engineer for Expedition 36 and ISS Commander for Expedition 37.
NGC 413 is a spiral galaxy of type SB(r)c located in the constellation Cetus.

2033 Basilea was discovered on 6 February 1973, by astronomer Paul Wild at the Zimmerwald Observatory near Bern, Switzerland.
Soyuz TMA-19 undocked from ISS and landed in Kazakhstan on the November 26, 2010.
NGC 2403 (also known as Caldwell 7) is an intermediate spiral galaxy in the constellation Camelopardalis.
31192 Aigoual was discovered on 29 December 1997, by staff members of the Pises Observatory in southern France.

(277810) 2006 FV, provisional designation 2006 FV, is a sub-kilometer near-Earth asteroid in the dynamical Apollo asteroid group, discovered by Spacewatch at Kitt Peak National Observatory, Arizona, on 29 March 2006.
NGC 377 is a spiral galaxy located in the constellation Cetus.
Soyuz TMA-18M was a 2015 Soyuz spaceflight to the International Space Station.
2001 Einstein was discovered by Swiss astronomer Paul Wild at Zimmerwald Observatory near Bern, Switzerland, on 5 March 1973.
NGC 2460 is a spiral galaxy in the constellation Camelopardalis.
ISOHDFS 27 is a spiral galaxy in the constellation Tucana, and was discovered in the Hubble Deep Field South survey.
7317 Cabot was discovered on 12 March 1940, by Hungarian astronomer GyÃ¶rgy Kulin at the Konkoly Observatory in Budapest.

NGC 4506 is a spiral galaxy located around 50 million light-years away in the constellation Coma Berenices.

Thomas David Jones flew on STS-59 and STS-68 in 1994, STS-80 in 1996 and STS-98 in 2001.
NGC 336 is a spiral galaxy in the constellation Cetus.
NGC 4689 is a spiral galaxy located about 54 million light-years away in the constellation of Coma Berenices.
3551 Verenia, provisional designation 1983 RD, is an Amor asteroid and a Mars crosser discovered on 12 September 1983 by R. Scott Dunbar.
The asteroid was discovered on 30 December 1965, by astronomers at the Purple Mountain Observatory in Nanking, China, and named after the city of Shanghai.

First observed in 1962, 3494 Purple Mountain was officially discovered on 7 December 1980, by Chinese astronomers at the Purple Mountain Observatory in Nanking, China, and later named in honor of the discovering observatory.
NGC 6104 is a barred spiral galaxy located in the constellation Corona Borealis.
The mission launched on March 23rd, 2016 at 11:05 PM.
NGC 291 is a barred spiral galaxy in the constellation Cetus.
NGC 3631 is a spiral galaxy located in the constellation Ursa Major.
NGC 303 is a lenticular galaxy in the constellation Cetus.
NGC 320 is a spiral galaxy in the constellation Cetus.
1863 Antinous was discovered on 7 March 1948 by American astronomer Carl Wirtanen at Lick Observatory on the summit of Mount Hamilton, California.
Poindexter was selected in the 1998 NASA Group (G17) and went into orbit aboard Space Shuttle missions STS-122 and STS-131.
